  "prompt": "How do I A2A a Quora user?",
  "response": "On Quora, A2A stands for \"Ask to Answer.\" To A2A a Quora user, follow these steps:\n\n1. Navigate to the question you want an answer to.\n2. If you're not already following the question, click \"Follow\" below the question to follow it.\n3. Click on the \"Ask to Answer\" button, which is usually located below the question title or in the options menu (three dots) near the question title.\n4. A window will open where you can search for the user you want to request an answer from. You can type their name in the search field.\n5. Select the user from the list that appears.\n6. You can also optionally add a personalized message to your request.\n7. Click \"Send\" to complete the A2A request.\n\nThe user will receive a notification about your request and can choose to answer the question if they are interested.",
